<item>
            <title>[HBASE-9690] HBase Mirrors are missing md5 and sha1 checksums for tarballs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9690</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently there is no way to verify the integrity of release tarballs. Please provide md5, sha1 and gpg signatures, so that users can be sure, that they have the correct tarball.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Many open source projects provide the above and hbase would benefit from that as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This looks like the right solution for the problem:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://nicoulaj.github.io/checksum-maven-plugin/examples/generating-project-artifacts-checksums.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://nicoulaj.github.io/checksum-maven-plugin/examples/generating-project-artifacts-checksums.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12671569">HBASE-9690</key>
            <summary>HBase Mirrors are missing md5 and sha1 checksums for tarballs</summary>
