                            <comment id="13782947" author="jmspaggi" created="Tue, 1 Oct 2013 13:51:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Andr&#233;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Each release come with its MD5 and it&apos;s always verified by the community that the MD5 matchs the provided files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you please detail exactly what is missing? Have you looked in the download section from the main site?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JM&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13782951" author="jmspaggi" created="Tue, 1 Oct 2013 13:56:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can take a look here as an example: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.us.apache.org/dist/hbase/hbase-0.94.12/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.us.apache.org/dist/hbase/hbase-0.94.12/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13782954" author="fs111" created="Tue, 1 Oct 2013 14:03:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems, that the mirrors are lacking those files:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Examples:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://mirror.serversupportforum.de/apache/hbase/hbase-0.94.12/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://mirror.serversupportforum.de/apache/hbase/hbase-0.94.12/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://ftp.halifax.rwth-aachen.de/apache/hbase/hbase-0.94.12/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://ftp.halifax.rwth-aachen.de/apache/hbase/hbase-0.94.12/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://apache.mirror.iphh.net/hbase/hbase-0.94.12/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://apache.mirror.iphh.net/hbase/hbase-0.94.12/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13783026" author="jmspaggi" created="Tue, 1 Oct 2013 15:02:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok. So it&apos;s more an issue with the mirrors than with the HBase repository.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems to be missing from most of the mirrors but some still have it like &lt;a href=&quot;http://apache.sunsite.ualberta.ca/hbase/hbase-0.95.2/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://apache.sunsite.ualberta.ca/hbase/hbase-0.95.2/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Strange. But most probably not HBase related. I will bring that to the mailing list.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13788055" author="fs111" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2013 10:46:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;any news on this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13788096" author="jmspaggi" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2013 12:02:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still not. I re-asked...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13788292" author="jmspaggi" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2013 16:34:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/INFRA-6848&quot; title=&quot;Some mirrors are not replicating the .MD5 files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;INFRA-6848&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;INFRA-6848&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13789693" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Tue, 8 Oct 2013 20:59:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hashes should be downloaded from the ASF mirror only; see for example &lt;a href=&quot;http://httpd.apache.org/download.cgi&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://httpd.apache.org/download.cgi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that PGP / MD5 / SHA1 all link to www.apachae.org/dist/httpd/...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15264807" author="busbey" created="Fri, 29 Apr 2016 21:39:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this as &quot;information provided&quot; because the earlier comment that checksums / signatures should be downloaded directly from www.apache.org/dist/hbase is correct.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
